# Traffic System — Technical Doc

## Concept
Background flavor only. Cars spawn at city entry points, drive through the city following a waypoint graph, despawn at exit points. No collision detection, no pathfinding — just waypoint chasing.

## Scripts
- `Waypoint.cs` — graph node. Stores next waypoints, flags, laneID
- `CarAgent.cs` — drives a car along the graph
- `CarSpawner.cs` — spawns and despawns cars

## Waypoint Flags
| Flag | Color | Behavior |
|------|-------|----------|
| default | yellow | normal node, pick random next |
| `isExit` | red | car despawns here (spawned cars) or loops to start (pre-placed) |
| `isStop` | blue | car rolls against `stopChance`, if wins it waits `minStopTime`-`maxStopTime` seconds before continuing |

## LaneID System
Prevents U-turns at intersections. Each waypoint has a `laneID` (default -1 = disabled).

**Rule:** when a car leaves a waypoint, it remembers that waypoint's laneID. At the next waypoint, it refuses to pick any exit with that same laneID.

**Convention used in ScarCity:**
- 0 = northbound
- 1 = southbound
- 2 = eastbound
- 3 = westbound
- -1 = no filtering (default, most waypoints)

**Intersection wiring:**
```
Entry WP (laneID=N) → Center WP (laneID=-1) → Exit WPs (laneID=0/1/2/3)
```
- Only entry WPs point to center
- Center points to all exits
- Exit WPs point forward down the road ONLY, never back to center

## Weighted Random
Adding the same waypoint multiple times in `nextWaypoints` increases its chance of being picked. e.g. Waypoint A listed twice + Waypoint B listed once = 2/3 chance of A, 1/3 chance of B.

## CarSpawner Setup
- Attach to empty GameObject in city scene
- Assign car prefabs (each needs `CarAgent.cs`, `isPrePlaced` unchecked)
- Assign entry waypoints (the off-screen road entry points)
- `maxCars` — total cars in city at once
- `spawnInterval` — seconds between spawns

## City-Specific Setup
- 3 off-screen roads, all going same direction
- 2 entry roads, 1 dedicated exit road
- Single lane per road (two-lane was scrapped, too complex for background flavor)
- Waypoints placed every ~60 units on straights (3 road tiles), denser at intersections
- All waypoints parented under a `Waypoints` empty GameObject in hierarchy
- All waypoints at Y=0 (road surface is technically -5.245367e-06, doesn't matter)

## Stop Locations
- Bus stop
- Gas station
- Pizza place (T-junction stop, cars can pull in from both directions)

## Key Technical Notes
- No collision avoidance — cars phase through each other, nobody notices from game camera height
- `isPrePlaced = true` on CarAgent makes it loop back to `startWaypoint` on exit instead of despawning — not currently used since all cars are spawner-managed
- Dead-end waypoints (no next waypoints) log a warning and deactivate the car
- CarAgent uses `_incomingLaneID` to track last known laneID — `-1` waypoints don't overwrite it, so the last real laneID persists through `-1` nodes
- `StopRoutine` is a coroutine — use `yield break` not `return` for early exits

